{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1cbd0e9e-4cf6-4887-92bf-072f8a55ce8a","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively** when it detects an MTP project. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt in, but in .NET 10 it's the default and can be removed.\n\nYour project already has `EnableMSTestRunner`, which is what makes it an MTP project. Just drop the now-unnecessary property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01G8U75cEAUBdTgA2ojwL24x","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1ff324bd42b444d0919681a5b8ec666a/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1ff324bd42b444d0919681a5b8ec666a/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"0f21022e-da30-4e59-bd4d-44cef110eff4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner`. They have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform when the test project is an MTP project (i.e., uses `EnableMSTestRunner` or similar). The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into the MTP integration with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10, this is the default behavior.\n\n\nSince `dotnet test` now uses MTP by default in .NET 10, the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is redundant and can be removed from their project file. The `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still necessary to configure the test project as an MTP executable.","outputTokens":549,"requestId":"5C32:33CB43:BF9CD:F1C05:69F54BED"},"id":"4de1b7b0-7588-4427-874c-fa5df773efce","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:57:28.367Z","parentId":"4f2120f1-0fc0-4e04-a39d-40c61ad1a612"}
